api_list.name: /customers/{customerId}/orders
api_list.description:
Returns a list of all your orders.

Use this to see all orders you have ever placed with the system. Orders in all states will be shown, including canceled orders.

This command allows you to search the list of orders by various filter parameters.

required_parameters.name: customerId
required_parameters.description: The id of the customer object of your account

optional_parameters.name: productId
optional_parameters.description: Optionally filter order results by the product type. Acceptable values list

optional_parameters.name: countryCode
optional_parameters.description: An ISO Alpha2 or ISO Alpha3 country code by which to filter results

optional_parameters.name: connectionType
optional_parameters.description: Optionally filter order results by the connection type in use. Acceptable values list = [pstn, direct]

optional_parameters.name: status
optional_parameters.description: Optionally filter order results by the status; accepted values

optional_parameters.name: requestId
optional_parameters.description: Any value meaningful to you that correlated orders together

api_list.name: /customers/{customerId}/orders/{orderId}
api_list.description:
Returns a specific order, identified by its id.

Use this to see a specific order you have placed with the system.

required_parameters.name: customerId
required_parameters.description: The id of the customer object of your account
